Title: Sugar
Synopsis: Two influencers find themselves on a luxury cruise through the Caribbean and South Pacific. But as the mirage of their online personas starts clashing with their real-life ambitions, a battle of wills threatens to tear them apart.

Title: Moh
Synopsis: A teenage boy Rabbi falls in love with an orchestra girl Gore who's living a tragic life while their relationship leads to various destruction for lifetime.

Title: Play Dead
Synopsis: Chloe fakes her own death to steal evidence from a morgue. The Coroner uses the morgue as a front for a sick and twisted business. A scary game of cat and mouse ensues as Chloe learns more about the dead than she bargains for.

Title: Cadaver
Synopsis: A high profile murder baffles the cops when a prison inmate claims responsibility and promises more deaths. Will the police surgeon Bhadra crack this mystery?

Title: Matriarch
Synopsis: Afflicted with a mysterious disease after surviving an overdose, a woman returns to her childhood home to confront her personal demons but instead discovers a real one.

Title: Kooman
Synopsis: The story is about a strict police officer who relocates to a hilly village on the Kerala-Tamil Nadu border. Few normal incidents that take place suddenly appear to be abnormal.

Title: Lost in the Stars
Synopsis: He Fei's wife, Li Muzi, disappears during their anniversary trip. When she reappears, he insists that she is not his wife. As Chen Mai, a top lawyer gets involved in this bizarre case, more mysteries start to emerge.

Title: Old People
Synopsis: A woman travels home with her two kids for her sister's wedding but finds herself defending her family against blood-seeking pensioners.

Title: The Magic Flute
Synopsis: Follows 17-year-old Tim Walker as he travels from London to the Austrian Alps to attend the legendary Mozart boarding school. There, he discovers a centuries-old forgotten passageway into the fantastic world of Mozart's "The Magic Flute."

Title: Raksha Bandhan
Synopsis: Lala Kedarnath promises his dying mother to marry his 4 sisters well. Owner of family chat shop, he has trouble finding suitors. His sisters take priority over childhood romance with Sapna.

Title: Renegades
Synopsis: When a retired Green Beret soldier is murdered by an international drug gang in London, four of his veteran SAS comrades set out to avenge him, dispensing their own brand of justice on the streets of London.

Title: Final Cut
Synopsis: Things go badly for a small film crew shooting a low budget zombie movie when they are attacked by real zombies.

Title: Remember Member
Synopsis: A high school student and her friends are trapped in a time loop by a ghost and the only way to escape is to find the corpse of the ghost's previous victim.

Title: God's Country
Synopsis: When a college professor confronts two hunters she catches trespassing on her property, she's drawn into an escalating battle of wills with catastrophic consequences.

Title: The Man from Rome
Synopsis: Vatican intelligence officer Father Quart (Richard Armitage) investigates a message sent to the pope about a crumbling Spanish church that "kills to defend itself." A deep conspiracy unfolds that challenges the Father's loyalty and faith.

Title: Bubble
Synopsis: After bubbles that broke the laws of gravity rained down upon the world. Cut off from the outside world, Tokyo has become a playground for a group of young people who have lost their families.

Title: Nude Tuesday
Synopsis: A suburban couple goes to a new-age retreat as a last ditch attempt to save their marriage. Their path to reconnection is riddled with hilarity and humiliation as they seek to find themselves and each other.

Title: Runway 34
Synopsis: Inspired by true incidents, "Runway 34" revolves around Captain Vikrant Khanna played by Ajay Devgn, a flying prodigy, whose flight takes a mysterious course after take-off from an international destination.

Title: Gold Run
Synopsis: Based on the true story of the effort to evacuate the entire Norwegian gold reserve out of Norway during the German invasion of Norway in World War II to keep the gold out of Germany's hands.

Title: The Lost Girls
Synopsis: Like her grandmother and her mother Jane before her, Wendy must escape Pan's hold on her and the promise he wants her to keep.

Title: Both Sides of the Blade
Synopsis: A love triangle story about a woman caught between two men, her long-time partner and his best friend, her former lover.

Title: Trenque Lauquen
Synopsis: With the strange disappearance of Laura, two colleagues, her older boyfriend, Rafael, and Ezequiel, learn of their recent discoveries, which may help them locate her. However, the story is bigger and stranger than they could imagine.

Title: Deer Camp '86
Synopsis: In the fall of 1986, six knuckleheads from Detroit travel north to partake in the annual tradition of deer hunting. But something horrific has been awakened and the hunters become the hunted.

Title: Shin Ultraman
Synopsis: As the threat of giant unidentified lifeforms known as "S-Class Species" worsens in Japan, a silver giant appears from beyond Earth's atmosphere.

Title: Simone Veil, a Woman of the Century
Synopsis: Explores the life of Simone Veil -- the famous French figure who survived the Holocaust and went on to become a leading politician, human rights campaigner, and feminist -- through a series of non-chronological memories

Title: Mascarade
Synopsis: Adrien, an attractive dancer whose career was shattered by a motorcycle accident, squanders his youth in idleness. His life changes when he meets Margot, who lives off scams and amorous manipulations.

Title: Salute
Synopsis: S.I Aravind Karunakaran, a police officer on voluntary leave, is haunted by an old case he investigated. How far will he go to unravel the mystery and bring the truth to light?

Title: The Visitor
Synopsis: After a series of tragedies, Robert moves with his wife back to her childhood home. After he discovers an old portrait of a man who looks like him, he goes down a rabbit hole to discover the identity of this mysterious doppelganger.

Title: Blank
Synopsis: A desperate writer signs up for a fully A.I. operated retreat to cure her writer's block, but when an unforeseen software glitch occurs, she gets trapped inside her unit with an unstable android and no communication with the outside world.

Title: Mad Heidi
Synopsis: Swiss mountain girl Heidi is abducted by brutal government troops and must defend herself and fight a war against a cheese-fueled machinery of hate.

Title: Linoleum
Synopsis: When the host of a failing children's science show endeavors to achieve his childhood dream of becoming an astronaut by constructing a rocket ship in his garage, a series of bizarre events occur that cause him to question his own reality.

Title: The Takeover
Synopsis: Framed for murder after uncovering a privacy scandal, an ethical hacker must evade the police while trying to track down the criminals blackmailing her.

Title: Glorious
Synopsis: After a breakup, Wes ends up at a remote rest stop. He finds himself locked inside the bathroom with a mysterious figure speaking from an adjacent stall. Soon Wes realizes he is involved in a situation more terrible than he could imagine.

Title: The Innocent
Synopsis: When Abel learns that his mother is about to marry a man in prison, he freaks out. With the help of his best friend, he will do whatever it takes to protect her. But meeting his new stepfather may well offer him a new perspective.

Title: The Grump: In Search of an Escort
Synopsis: The Grump goes to search for a second-hand car in Germany to replace his broken one but ends up settling accounts with his past.

Title: Goliath
Synopsis: Patrick is a tenacious lawyer specializing in environmental law. France is a schoolteacher who becomes an activist after her husband develops cancer from exposure to a pesticide. Mathias is an ambitious lobbyist for a chemical corporation.

Title: Vadh
Synopsis: After their son moves to USA, a middle-class married couple is relentlessly harassed by a loan shark.

Title: The Apology
Synopsis: Twenty years after the disappearance of her daughter, a recovering alcoholic is preparing to host her family's Christmas celebration when her estranged ex-brother-in-law arrives unannounced, bearing nostalgic gifts and a heavy secret.

Title: Delia's Gone
Synopsis: A convicted man embarks on a journey of violence and redemption to find out the truth about his sister's death.

Title: My Fake Boyfriend
Synopsis: In the film, a young man in a tricky situation (Keiynan Lonsdale) follows the advice of his unconventional best friend (Dylan Sprouse) and uses social media to create a fake boyfriend to keep his awful ex-lover out of his life. But everything backfires when he meets the real love of his life, and breaking up with his fake boyfriend proves hard to do.

Title: Detective Knight: Rogue
Synopsis: As Los Angeles prepares for Halloween, mask-wearing armed robbers critically wound detective James Knight's partner in a shootout following a heist.

Title: Pacifiction
Synopsis: On the French Polynesian island of Tahiti, the high commissioner of the Republic and French government must investigate an ongoing rumor: the sighting of a submarine whose ghostly presence could herald the return of French nuclear testing.

Title: Big Gold Brick
Synopsis: Fledgling writer Samuel Liston and his experiences with Floyd Deveraux, the enigmatic middle-aged father of two who enlists Samuel to write his biography.

Title: Three Months
Synopsis: Coming-of-age film about Caleb, a South Florida teen. On the eve of his high school graduation, everything changes when he's exposed to HIV. While he waits three months for his results, he finds love in the most unlikely of places.

Title: Alcarràs
Synopsis: The life of a family of peach farmers in a small village in Catalonia changes when the owner of their large estate dies and his lifetime heir decides to sell the land, suddenly threatening their livelihood.

Title: My Son Hunter
Synopsis: Fictional retelling of the lifestyle and scandals of Hunter Biden, son of US President Joe Biden.

Title: Tantura
Synopsis: In the war of 1948 hundreds of Palestinian villages were depopulated. Israelis call it 'The War of Independence. Palestinians call it 'Nakba"'. The film examines one village- Tantura and why "Nakba" is taboo in Israeli society.

Title: My Sailor, My Love
Synopsis: A retired sea captain and his daughter must reassess their strained relationship after he begins a new romance with a widowed housekeeper.

Title: White Elephant
Synopsis: An ex-marine enforcer must battle his conscience and code of honor when he is forced to do things for the mob.

Title: Taurus
Synopsis: Follows the last days of a rising but problematic musician.

Title: Relax, I'm from the Future
Synopsis: A man from the future, now trapped in the past, tries to make a life for himself, oblivious to the consequences he has set in motion.

Title: Blade of the 47 Ronin
Synopsis: Ancient Japanese Ronin warriors set 300 years after 47 Ronin, in a modern-day world where Samurai clans exist in complete secrecy.

Title: All That Breathes
Synopsis: Amidst the darkening backdrop of Delhi's apocalyptic air and escalating violence, two brothers devote their lives to protect one casualty of the turbulent times: the bird known as the Black Kite.

Title: Bhoothakaalam
Synopsis: Following the death of a family member, a mother and son experience mysterious events which distort their sense of reality and make them question their sanity.

Title: Carnifex
Synopsis: An aspiring documentarian and two conservationists who venture into the Outback to record the animals displaced by bushfires where they discover a terrifying new species.

Title: Pink Moon
Synopsis: When a young woman receives the absurd news from her father that he's had enough of life and wants it to come to an end, she is forced to search for a way to deal with his last wish.

Title: Hilma
Synopsis: Exploring Hilma af Klint's enigmatic life, now recognized as one of the Western world's first abstract artists.

Title: Dive
Synopsis: Mariel is a veteran elite diver who has one last chance at the Olympic Games. However, when a terrible truth comes to light, Mariel faces her biggest personal question: Is winning her true dream?

Title: Overdose
Synopsis: Follows Sara, head of the Toulouse police narcotics squad, who is forced to collaborate with Richard, the head of the local criminal police, to stop a go-fast between Spain and France and find the murderer linked to the case.

Title: Men of Deeds
Synopsis: Ilie (late 30s) enjoys the easy life of a village policeman. His passivity during a series of violent events soon turns him into an accomplice to murder. Tension accumulates in the village, forcing Ilie to make a final decision.

Title: Fourth of July
Synopsis: A recovering alcoholic and jazz pianist in NYC confronts his acerbic family during their annual Fourth of July vacation.

Title: Shark Side of the Moon
Synopsis: Decades ago, the USSR developed unkillable sharks and launched them to the moon. Today, a team of American astronauts will endure the fight of their lives.

Title: 1UP
Synopsis: Follows a gamer who quits her college esports team due to sexism from her male counterparts.

Title: Stowaway
Synopsis: A tenacious party girl fights to survive after three thieves commandeer her luxury yacht. Unable to escape and trapped on the yacht at high seas, she turns the tables on the intruders and takes matters into her own hands.

Title: The Abandon
Synopsis: A wounded soldier awakens in a strange cube that tests his physical and mental limits as he attempts to find a way to escape against a ticking clock.

Title: Girl Picture
Synopsis: As three young women try to defy the persistent winter darkness in Finland, they move between dreams, reality, friendship, and relationships, and try to make sense of everything.

Title: Master
Synopsis: Three women strive to find their place at an elite Northeastern university. When anonymous racist attacks target a Black freshman, who insists she is being haunted by ghosts, each woman must determine where the real menace lies.

Title: Grand Expectations
Synopsis: Summer 2019. Just graduated, Madeleine goes to Corsica to prepare for further exams with Antoine, her lover with whom she shares very left-wing political convictions. On a small deserted road, an unexpected encounter will seal their fate.

Title: Unplugging
Synopsis: To revive their marriage and reconnect, a couple takes a self-prescribed digital detox weekend to a remote mountain town. What starts as a perfect weekend getaway without technology quickly spirals out of control.

Title: Showroom
Synopsis: Liezel, an ambitious agent, learns that her colleague, Susan, uses her body to sell condo units; so she imitates her scheme. When the tables turn, Liezel begins to face her punishments one by one.

Title: North of Normal
Synopsis: After being raised in the wilderness, a teenage girl moves to the city hoping for a normal life with her anything but normal mother.

Title: Kaguya-sama: Love Is War - The First Kiss That Never Ends
Synopsis: Now that Kaguya and Miyuki have shared their first kiss, the time has come for them to truly understand each other and admit their feelings.

Title: Code Name: Emperor
Synopsis: Follows Juan, an agent working for the intelligence services, who also reports to a parallel unit involved in illegal activities.

Title: Chup - The Revenge of an Artist
Synopsis: A lonesome florist with a new-found love interest and a psychopath killer who targets film critics in Mumbai. Are the two related? Inspector Arvind Mathur and Dr. Zenobia are about to find out.

Title: Ponniyin Selvan
Synopsis: Vandiyathevan crosses the Chola land to deliver a message from the Crown Prince Aditha Karikalan, while Kundavai attempts to establish political peace as vassals and petty chieftains plot against the throne.

Title: The Last 10 Years
Synopsis: Twenty-year-old Matsuri Takabayashi learns that she only has ten years to live due to an incurable disease. She decides to not dwell on her life and not to fall in love, but she meets Kazuto Manabe at a school reunion.

Title: American Murderer
Synopsis: Charismatic con man Jason Derek Brown becomes wanted by the FBI after hatching his most elaborate scheme yet.

Title: Rebel
Synopsis: A portrayal of a family torn apart over a little Muslim boy's future.

Title: The Fire That Took Her
Synopsis: The case of Judy Malinowski, a young mother who suffered debilitating burns after being set on fire by a man she had dated.

Title: Attachment
Synopsis: Maja, a Danish has-been actress, falls in love with Leah, a Jewish academic from London. Leah suffers a mysterious seizure, and Maja returns with her to London. There, she meets Leah's mother, Chana, a woman who could hold dark secrets.

Title: Maigret
Synopsis: In Paris, a young girl is found dead in a Parisian square, wearing an evening dress. Commissioner Maigret will try to identify her and then understand what happened to the victim.

Title: Sarkaru Vaari Paata
Synopsis: After being conned by the woman he loves, a finance agent arrives in India from USA to retrieve his money from the woman's father who is a powerful MP and industrialist.

Title: Decibel
Synopsis: The story unfolds when a bomb that responds to sound is discovered at the center of the city.

Title: The Passengers of the Night
Synopsis: Left by her husband, Elisabeth finds herself alone, responsible for the day-to-day care of her two children. She picks up a job on a night-time radio show, where she meets Talulah, a youngster she decides to take under her wing.

Title: The Loneliest Boy in the World
Synopsis: 'The Loneliest Boy in the World' is a modern fairytale - with zombies. A satire and a celebration of family values, of the imagery of horror films, of suburban life, of the American Dream and of the ultimate taboo; death.

Title: Chernobyl 86
Synopsis: Newly-discovered archive footage and witness accounts to lay bare the tragedy and heroic efforts made to prevent another explosion.

Title: Terror Train
Synopsis: It follows a college student as she boards a party train for Halloween, and ends up fighting for her life when a mysterious assailant begins killing the people one-by-one.

Title: This Place Rules
Synopsis: Follows events and characters surrounding the January 6th, 2021 insurrection of the U.S. Capital Building in the days preceding the attack.

Title: Dolphin Boy
Synopsis: Dolphin Snowball rescues a little boy in the waves. Since then, they carelessly grow up together, exciting the marine life with their funny tricks. But one day, the peace of their joyful little world is destroyed by the evil Octopus.

Title: Your Christmas or Mine?
Synopsis: Hayley and James are young and in love. They both make the same mad split-second decision to swap trains and surprise each other. Passing each other in the station, they are completely unaware that they have just swapped Christmases.

Title: Blaze
Synopsis: After accidentally witnessing a violent crime, a young girl is left catatonic with shock, and struggles to make sense of what she saw, ultimately finding renewal in the inestimable world of her own imagination.

Title: The Honeymoon
Synopsis: Adam and his bride, Sarah are about to embark on the romantic honeymoon of a lifetime in Venice. But when the trip is gatecrashed by Adam's best friend, Ed, it inadvertently turns their perfect lovers' holiday into a complete disaster.

Title: Eyes on Fire
Synopsis: Take a peek at the life of an unhappy housewife who finds passionate love from her neighbor and how their affair brings them closer to fire.

Title: I Heard the Bells
Synopsis: The inspiring story behind the writing of the beloved Christmas carol and its author, Henry Wadsworth Longfellow.

Title: Mann Kasturi Re
Synopsis: Worlds collide when rich girl Shruti falls in love with middle class boy Siddhant. She is full of life and charming while he is quiet and sweet. Siddhant is serious about his career and looking after his mother. However Shruti convinces him to get into a relationship with her and he agrees. Everything looks hunky-dory until that one night that changes everything.

Title: L'immensità
Synopsis: The story of love between Clara and her children, set in Rome in the '70s.

Title: Incredible But True
Synopsis: Alain and Marie moved to the suburb house of their dreams. But the real estate agent warned them: what is in the basement may well change their lives forever.

Title: Out of the Darkness
Synopsis: Strong and dramatic sequel to "Into the Darkness" which follows the Skov family from 1943 to the end of WWII. The growing opposition to the occupation and the increased brutality of the Germans have fatal consequences for the family.

Title: Filip
Synopsis: In 1943, a Polish Jew, who managed to escape from the Warsaw ghetto, is waiting restaurant tables in Frankfurt while pretending to be French and taking revenge on the Nazis in his own unique way.

Title: Leave
Synopsis: A young woman tries to find her origins after having been abandoned as an infant at a cemetery wrapped in a cloth with satanic symbols, but as she gets closer to answers a malevolent spirit is telling her to leave.

Title: Can They See Us?
Synopsis: Rejected by his father at birth, a boy with albinism navigates a childhood of bullying, tragedy and cautious hope in this coming-of-age drama.

Title: Saint Omer
Synopsis: Follows Rama, a novelist who attends the trial of Laurence Coly at the Saint-Omer Criminal Court to use her story to write a modern-day adaptation of the ancient myth of Medea, but things don't go as expected.

Title: Ved
Synopsis: After being abandoned by his lover, Satya finds himself entangled with alcohol and to overcome the grief his childhood lover and neighbour Shravani decides to marry him.

Title: Amerikatsi
Synopsis: Charlie escapes the Armenian genocide as a boy by fleeing to the United States, but he returns as an adult and is arrested. He watches an Armenian couple from his prison cell, finally learning about his homeland.

Title: Family Camp
Synopsis: In this faith-based comedy, when two polar-opposite families are forced to camp together, the dads struggle to hold onto their families and marriages as they compete for the coveted camp trophy.

Title: Nna, Thaan Case Kodu
Synopsis: A reformed thief's fight for justice when an innocent act to defend himself places him in loggerheads with the high and mighty of society.

Title: Major
Synopsis: Based on the life of Major Sandeep Unnikrishnan, who fought during the November 2008 Mumbai attacks.

Title: Good Night Oppy
Synopsis: The film follows Opportunity, the Mars Exploration Rover affectionately dubbed Oppy by her creators and scientists at NASA. Oppy was originally expected to live for only 90 days but she ultimately explored Mars for nearly 15 years.

Title: Rocketry: The Nambi Effect
Synopsis: The story of Indian Space Research Organization scientist Nambi Narayanan, who was framed for being a spy and arrested in 1994.

Title: Elsker dig for tiden
Synopsis: Anna and Thomas are missing something: love. They will follow their encounter through confusing crushes and lack of commitment, but can love survive when you don't want to compromise your own dreams for your partner?

Title: The Tiger's Nest
Synopsis: Orphan Balmani rescues tiger cub Mukti from cruel hunters, and together they set off on an adventure to find a safe home for Mukti.

Title: Rise
Synopsis: Elise, a very promising classical dancer, is injured during a performance at 26 years old. Although she's told she will no longer be able to dance, she will try to find a new direction in contemporary dance.

Title: Confidential Assignment 2: International
Synopsis: The film depicts an unpredictable global cooperative investigation by South Korean, North Korean, and American detectives who have come together for their own purposes.

Title: She Is Love
Synopsis: Coming face-to-face after being estranged for over a decade, divorced couple Idris and Patricia opt to revisit the past and traverse that treacherous path together, emerging open to new beginnings.

Title: The Forger
Synopsis: Cioma Schönhaus, a 21-year-old Jewish man, escapes the Gestapo and saves lives thanks to his ability to forge passports. His other talent is forging his own identity.

Title: Satan's Slaves 2: Communion
Synopsis: When the heavy storm hits, it wasn't the storm that a family should fear but the people and non-human entities who are out for them.

Title: Impuratus
Synopsis: 1930s Pennsylvania, a weary detective (Tom Sizemore) on the verge of losing faith in humanity confronts a malevolent force within an asylum when an aged war veteran insists on confessing dark secrets that threatens his family.

Title: Broad Peak
Synopsis: After climbing Broad Peak mountain, Maciej Berbeka learns his journey to the summit is incomplete. 25 years later, he sets out to finish what he started.

Title: The Jesuit
Synopsis: A man nicknamed "the Jesuit," is imprisoned for a crime he didn't commit. When his wife is murdered and his son kidnapped and taken to Mexico, he devises an elaborate and dangerous plan to rescue his son and avenge the murder.

Title: Dracula: The Original Living Vampire
Synopsis: Amelia Van Helsing is on the desperate hunt for the killer responsible for a string of grisly murders targeting young women. Her prime suspect: the mysterious Count Dracula.

Title: Yashoda
Synopsis: In a highly regimented facility housing surrogate mothers, a pregnant woman discovers that things are not as they seem.

Title: Kids vs. Aliens
Synopsis: An all-time rager of a teen house party turns to terror when aliens attack, forcing two warring siblings to band together to survive the night.

Title: Scrooge: A Christmas Carol
Synopsis: A supernatural, time-travelling, musical adaptation of Charles Dickens's cult Christmas story.

Title: The Almond and the Seahorse
Synopsis: What happens when you're ambushed by time? An archaeologist and an architect fight to re-imagine a future after traumatic brain injury leaves them adrift from the people they love.

Title: Looking for Her
Synopsis: Taylor is headed home for the holidays and her family is finally ready to meet her girlfriend Jess--but Jess isn't her girlfriend anymore. Taylor holds open auditions for someone to play the part for the holidays.

Title: UFO Sweden
Synopsis: A rebellious teen placed in foster care suspects her father is not dead but has been abducted. She is determined to find out the truth with help from a UFO association.

Title: Lekh
Synopsis: Fate draws high-school sweethearts, Rajvir and Ronak apart only to bring the star-crossed lovers eye to eye again as adults who must work out their past and get closure before fate strikes again.

Title: The Origin of Evil
Synopsis: A woman on the verge of financial collapse attempts to impersonate her imprisoned lover and con her wealthy, estranged father and his new family.

Title: Spoonful of Sugar
Synopsis: Millicent is taking a semester off from her studies to take care of Johnny, a sickly, mute child with severe allergies. His mother, Rebecca, is an author and his father, Jacob, is a carpenter.

Title: Dangerous Liaisons
Synopsis: Book smart Célène falls for bad boy Tristan at her new Biarritz high school, unaware she's part of a cruel bet he's made with social media queen Vanessa.

Title: Dakota
Synopsis: Kate, a widow who lost her husband in the war in Afghanistan, struggles to maintain her small-town farm with her daughter while also running the local volunteer fire department.

Title: Who Invited Them
Synopsis: Two couples bond at a housewarming party. The hosts become suspicious when the lingering guests reveal wealth and continue drinking into the night.

Title: Drifting Home
Synopsis: Follows two childhood friends who drift into a mysterious sea with an entire housing complex.

Title: Civil Twilight
Synopsis: When the power mysteriously fails and almost everyone disappears from a tourist ship in the Arctic, fear becomes the master for the three who remain. Forced ashore, the men deteriorate in body and mind until a dark truth emerges.

Title: Zwigato
Synopsis: A man works as a food delivery rider, grappling with the world of ratings and incentives. To support the income, his homemaker wife begins to explore different work opportunities, with fear but also excitement of a new found independence.

Title: Peter von Kant
Synopsis: Peter Von Kant, a successful, famous director, lives with his assistant Karl, whom he likes to mistreat and humiliate. Through the great actress Sidonie, he meets and falls in love with Amir, a handsome young man of modest means.

Title: The Volcano: Rescue from Whakaari
Synopsis: Portrays human bravery and resilience after a tragic volcano disaster in New Zealand.

Title: Prizefighter: The Life of Jem Belcher
Synopsis: At the turn of the 19th century, Pugilism was the sport of kings and a gifted young boxer fought his way to becoming champion of England.

Title: November
Synopsis: 5 days into the heart of the French anti-terrorism services during the hunt for suspects after the 13/11/2015 attacks in Paris.

Title: Is That Black Enough for You?!?
Synopsis: Tracks the history of Black cinema, focused mainly on the '70s, with archival and new interviews with many of the key players from the era.

Title: Borrego
Synopsis: Borrego follows a young botanist who relocates to a small desert town to study an invasive plant species. She must fight for her survival when she's kidnapped by an inexperienced drug mule after his ultralight plane crashes in the desert.

Title: Dark Glasses
Synopsis: Diana, a young woman who lost her sight, finds a guide in a Chinese boy named Chin. Together they will track down a dangerous killer through the darkness of Italy.

Title: Driving Madeleine
Synopsis: Madeleine, leaves small suburban to join a nursing home, on the other side of Paris. Charles, a taxi driver, comes to pick her and in no hurry to reach, she asks him to go through places of the capital, which have counted in her life.

Title: Lifemark
Synopsis: David's comfortable world is turned upside down when his birthmother unexpectedly reaches out to him, longing to meet the 18-year-old son she's only held once.

Title: Arthur, malédiction
Synopsis: Alex has been a fan of the Arthur and the Minimoys saga for years. When his friends offer him to go to the abandoned house where the film was shot, he accepts, unaware that they are about to fall into a plot.

Title: The Abandoned
Synopsis: When a mysterious corpse is found in a river, a distressed police officer delves into a string of grisly murders as danger quickly approaches.

Title: Death Hunt
Synopsis: A land developer and his girlfriend are hunted on a remote island for sport by three deranged locals.

Title: Aisha
Synopsis: While caught for years in Ireland's immigration system Aisha Osagie develops a close friendship with former prisoner Conor Healy. This friendship soon looks to be short lived as Aisha's future in Ireland comes under threat.

Title: Wolves of War
Synopsis: At the end of WWII, a tough British officer leads a band of Allied commandos into enemy territory in Bavaria on one last impossible mission to extract an American held hostage by the Germans.

Title: Christmas Bloody Christmas
Synopsis: It's Christmas Eve and Tori just wants to get drunk and party, but when a robotic Santa Claus at a nearby toy store goes haywire and begins a rampant killing spree through her small town, she's forced into a battle for survival.

Title: Bula
Synopsis: A woman, who owns a laundry shop, uses her clients' clothes to satisfy her sexual fantasies. When she meets a hot police officer, she wants to have him no matter what it takes.

Title: Mortal Kombat Legends: Snow Blind
Synopsis: As Kano and the Black Dragon wreak havoc around the globe, a young warrior named Kenshi will have to rise above his own limitations and take on the looming threat of Outworld.

Title: The Escort Wife
Synopsis: A wife who just had a miscarriage finds out that her husband is having an affair with a high-end escort. She turns into prostitution and will take her revenge.

Title: Scarlet
Synopsis: The emancipation of a woman over twenty years, between 1919 and 1939, a time of great inventions and great dreams.

Title: Ariel Phenomenon
Synopsis: The film follows a BBC war reporter and Harvard psychiatrist Dr. John Mack, whose careers were threatened by the investigation of the incident, as well as a former student who journeys back to the rural Ariel School.

Title: Love Tactics
Synopsis: An ad executive and a fashion designer-blogger don't believe in love, so they place a bet to make the other fall head over heels - with unusual tactics.

Title: Naadi Dosh
Synopsis: New generation love birds, Riddhi and Kevin, shrewdly tackle the issue of 'Naadi Dosh', an old and dogmatic faith.

Title: The Girl on the Mountain
Synopsis: When a reclusive backwoodsman finds a mute little girl wandering alone in the forest, he must protect her from the evil forces determined to end her life.

Title: Nightsiren
Synopsis: A young woman returns to her native mountain village, searching for answers about her troubled childhood, but as she tries to uncover the truth, ancient superstitions lead the villagers to accuse her of witchcraft and murder.

Title: Freddy
Synopsis: The lines between love and obsession blur in this romantic thriller packed with unpredictable twists and sharp turns.

Title: The Uncle
Synopsis: The film appears to be set in Yugoslavia in the late 1980s, as a family welcomes their beloved uncle, who has returned home from Germany for the holidays.

Title: A Man of Action

Title: The Last Kingdom: Seven Kings Must Die
Synopsis: In the wake of King Edward's death, Uhtred of Bebbanburg and his comrades adventure across a fractured kingdom in the hopes of uniting England at last.

Title: The Mother

Synopsis: In this moving comedic drama set in postwar Rome, a working-class wife and mother dreams of a better future. Winner of 6 Italian Academy Awards.

Synopsis: When Ray discovers that his wife is cheating on him, he decides he's going to kill himself. His plans suddenly change when a stranger mistakes him for a low-rent hitman.

Title: They Cloned Tyrone

Title: Good Grief

Title: Strays

Title: The Hill

Title: The Taste of Things

Title: The Passenger

Title: Freelance

Title: Hypnotic

Title: The Critic
Synopsis: A powerful London theater critic becomes entangled in a web of deceit and murder.

Title: Shazam! Fury of the Gods

Title: Leo

Title: Sharper

Title: Kandahar

Title: The Vourdalak

Title: The End We Start From

Title: Daddio

Title: The Long Game

Title: Cobweb

Title: The Boys in the Boat

Title: Migration

Title: Joy Ride

Title: To Catch a Killer

Title: The Boogeyman

Title: Limbo

Title: BlackBerry

Title: Baghead

Title: Suitable Flesh

Title: Wildcat

Title: Do Not Expect Too Much from the End of the World

Title: The Great Escaper
Synopsis: Bernard Jordan escapes from his care home to attend the 70th Anniversary of the D-Day Landings in France.

Title: The Other Zoey

Title: The Burial

Title: Eileen

Title: Tatami

Title: Foe

Title: Talchul: Project Silence

Synopsis: Fran, who likes to think about dying, makes the new guy at work laugh, which leads to dating and more. Now the only thing standing in their way is Fran herself.

Title: Heart of Stone
Synopsis: An intelligence operative for a shadowy global peacekeeping agency races to stop a hacker from stealing its most valuable and dangerous weapon.

Title: The Three Musketeers: D'Artagnan

Title: The Convert

Synopsis: The Lamberts must go deeper into The Further than ever before to put their demons to rest once and for all.

Title: No More Bets

Title: Trim Season

Title: A Creature Was Stirring

Title: All-Time High
Synopsis: A con artist in dire need of cash and a woman with a crypto fortune hit it off. Is she the target of his dreams, or is the scammer about to get scammed?

Title: Best. Christmas. Ever!
Synopsis: Friendships are put to the ultimate test over a boastful holiday newsletter.

Title: Englemageren
Synopsis: Detective Laura has been on sick leave after suffering from postpartum depression, but when she and her partner become involved in a case, it becomes increasingly clear that she herself is hiding a dark secret.

Title: She Is Conann
Synopsis: Conan's life at different stages is shown with a different aesthetic and rhythm from the Sumerian era to the near future.

Title: Greatest Days
Synopsis: A feature adaptation of the 'The Band' musical, featuring the songs of Take That.

Title: Renaissance: A Film by Beyoncé
Synopsis: Beyoncé in performance at her record-breaking RENAISSANCE World Tour, and the creative mastermind behind it.

Synopsis: Tensions rise when a couple stays at the home of a reclusive host, with the three entering an intimate battle to gain and reclaim territory.

Title: Once Upon a Crime
Synopsis: While at the royal ball with Cinderella, Little Red Riding Hood finds herself in the middle of a mystery. Can she solve the case before midnight strikes?

Title: Kathal: A Jackfruit Mystery

Title: Mission Raniganj
Synopsis: When a flood leaves dozens of workers trapped in a coal mine, an engineer embarks on a daring rescue mission to save them. Inspired by real events.

Title: Making Of

Title: The Successor

Title: Norwegian Dream

An unsympathetic, failed, and frustrated cricketer enters her life, gives her a new dream, and transforms her fate with the most innovative training, making her play for the Indian cricket team again, but this time as a bowler. Ghoomer is the new style of bowling they invent to bamboozle the opposition.

Title: Kisi Ka Bhai Kisi Ki Jaan

Title: Our Son

Title: Lousy Carter

Title: Snow Falls

Title: Soul Mates
Synopsis: Follows Allison and Jason, two unsuspecting strangers who must find their way out of a nightmarish maze where they were forced to get into as part of a twisted new dating service created to help them find their Soul Mate.

Title: Angela

Title: Abang Adik

Title: Atatürk I 1881-1919
Synopsis: Graduated from the military school as an idealist patriot, Mustafa Kemal is an officer in the Ottoman army who wears his uniform with pride. He comes to realise that the Ottoman Empire is slowly rotting.

Title: River
Synopsis: On a calm winter's day, a mountain inn becomes trapped in a time loop.

Title: The Exorcists
Synopsis: To save his family a father hires three expert exorcists to get rid of the demon possessing his child.

Title: Thank You for Coming

Title: Gray Matter

Title: Cassandro

Title: The Angry Black Girl and Her Monster
Synopsis: Vicaria's a brilliant teenager. After the brutal murder of her brother, she embarks on a dangerous journey to ressurect him.

Title: Jigarthanda Double X
Synopsis: In 1975, a filmmaker agrees to collaborate on a film with a gangster who wishes to become a famous actor.

Title: Aliens Abducted My Parents and Now I Feel Kinda Left Out

Title: Sid Is Dead
Synopsis: The story of a socially invisible high school senior who, after slipping up and getting the school's biggest bully suspended, realizes he may only have two weeks left to experience everything he's ever missed out on.

Title: Rosalie
Synopsis: The story of the first bearded lady attraction.

Title: The Eternal Memory
Synopsis: Augusto and Paulina have been together for 25 years. Eight years ago, he was diagnosed with Alzheimer's disease. Both fear the day he no longer recognizes her.

Title: Berlin

Title: Mastaney

Title: The Pigeon Tunnel

Title: Junkyard Dog

Title: Killer Book Club

Title: Barber

Title: Back on the Strip

Title: Itlu Mee Cinema
Synopsis:
In "Itlu mee cinema," we follow the journey of Ram (Abhiram), a talented software engineer with a burning passion for filmmaking. Driven by his love for movies, Ram takes a bold leap, leaving behind his stable job to pursue his dream of becoming a director. Alongside him are three close friends: Pawan, Manohar, and Krishna, each with their own aspirations within the film industry.

Despite their relentless efforts, the four friends face numerous challenges in their quest for opportunities in the competitive world of cinema. Rejected time and again by established studios, they decide to take matters into their own hands and opt for crowdfunding to finance their debut film.

Meanwhile, amidst the trials of filmmaking, Ram's personal life takes a turn as his girlfriend Janu (Vennela) proposes marriage, urging him to reconsider his priorities. Struggling to balance his passion for filmmaking and his relationship, Ram finds himself at a crossroads, torn between love and ambition.

As production begins on their independent film, the friends encounter a rollercoaster of setbacks and small victories. They navigate creative differences, financial constraints, and unexpected hurdles, testing their friendship and resolve. Through it all, they learn invaluable lessons about perseverance, collaboration, and the true meaning of chasing one's dreams.

The climax culminates on the premiere night of their film. Amidst a mix of anticipation and nervousness, they await the audience's verdict-a moment that will define their journey in the film industry. Will their passion project be embraced by audiences and critics alike, propelling them into stardom? Or will it mark the end of their aspirations, forcing them to reassess their futures?

In a heartfelt conclusion, the film not only explores the intricacies of the filmmaking process but also delves into the personal sacrifices and triumphs of its characters. As the credits roll, viewers are left pondering the unpredictable path to success and the enduring power of dreams.

Epilogue: The fate of Ram and Janu's love story and the ultimate success of their film remain open-ended, leaving audiences to imagine the characters' futures beyond the screen. "Pursuit of Dreams" is a testament to the indomitable spirit of aspiring filmmakers everywhere, reminding us that every dream is worth pursuing, no matter the obstacles along the way.

Synopsis: "Vikaasa Parva" follows the wild journey of Vikky (Vikas Chandra) a man born into wealth and privilege, whose life revolves around the pursuit of pleasure, fueled by his belief that drinking is his way of life. Surrounded by like-minded friends and a witty but seemingly indifferent wife, Vikky's world takes a dark turn. The turning point occurs when tragedy strikes, claiming the life of one of Vikky's dose friends. The incident forces him into a brief introspection, but soon he reverts to his old ways drowning his sorrows in alcohol and alienating those around him with arrogance and disdain, However, fate takes an unexpected turn when Vikas Chandra, in drunk mode, decides to take a shortcut route while heading to an event with his wife. This impulsive decision sets off a chain of events that will forever alter Vikky's life. The seemingly beneficial shortcut becomes a path filled with danger, leading Vikky and his wife into a series of unforeseen challenges. As they navigate the treacherous route, Vikky is confronted with his own demons, forcing him to confront the consequences of his reckless lifestyle. "Vikaasa Parva" explores themes of redemption, self-discovery, and the fragility of life. Will Vikas Chandra emerge from this hartowing experience a changed man, or will his arrogance continue to haunt him? This forms the rest of the story. In a gripping tale of survival and transformation, "Vikaasa Parva" takes audiences on an emotional roller coaster, questioning the choices we make and the unexpected turns that can shape our destinies.

Synopsis: Based on the true event of Bantala Rape Case that shook the socio-political notions of 90' West Bengal, Kingshuk Dey Directed film The Red Files deals with the story in two separate timeline, one strictly follows the events occurred in the 90s and other follows the life and endeavours of IPS officer Priti Rao, in the present days. Priti along with Anjan, Imraan, Taniqsha, Arka and Others aid tries to re-open the 1990s Bantala Rape Case File, as in the past with political aid and ardent bureaucratic support and of their lawyer Sohini, the rapists got free, and the three rape victims got no justice in the other hand. Such hidden and confidential files are called the red files. The Bantala Rape Case File is no exception indeed. This issue which took place in 1990, three women were brutally raped and murdered. Yet, due to an inadequate amount of proof, political pressure and bureaucratic pressure this file also remained suppressed for years and turned into a red file. Priti focuses on re-opening the case to summon proper punishment to the brutal rapists, still existing in the present days without any fear and Shane. Will she and her team be able to bring justice to the rape victims after so many years? The Red Files will depict the rest with much thrill and enthusiasm.

Synopsis: Acid attack survivor faces rejection. Pursues music despite challenges. Earns PhD, becomes music teacher. Uses voice to overcome prejudice. Demonstrates resilience and talent in face of adversity.

Title: Thalli Manasu
Synopsis: Jyothi, a widow who raised her son alone after her husband Janakiram's tragic accident, devoted her entire life to him. Despite her deep love for her son she unexpectedly stabs her son's heart.

Title: Praavinkoodu Shappu
Synopsis: Follows a murder that happened inside the toddy shop and the hilarious events surrounding the investigation.

Title: When It Rains in LA
Synopsis: Following an Eastern European girl's escape from trauma, she goes on a vacation with friends, where she confronts her unresolved past and the consequences of her relocation.

Title: Ennu Swantham Punyalan
Synopsis: Reluctant priest Thomas' life is disrupted when a young woman and a thief unexpectedly arrive at his church mansion, leading to a series of chaotic encounters that uncover connections and revelations amidst misunderstandings and dilemmas.

Title: Sangee
Synopsis: Baman seeks a reunion with old classmates, hoping for an interest-free loan. His friends, wise to his tricks, are wary. Can Baman charm them, or will he be turned away? A light, humorous story of friendship and schemes unfolds.

Title: Madraskaaran
Synopsis: A minor argument between two strangers escalates into a life-altering conflict, exploring how a seemingly insignificant event can drastically alter a person's perception and circumstances.

Title: Am Ah
Synopsis: When Stephen, a road construction supervisor, visits Kavantha, an enigmatic yet beautiful mountainside, he uncovers a series of heart-warming events that shows love in its purest form.

Title: Choo Mantar
Synopsis: Four friends decide to enter the morgan house looking for a secret treasure. The four discover that before independence the house belonged to a British employee named Morgan. What will happen next is not obvious.

Title: Anpodu Kanmani
Synopsis: A newlywed couple faces the amusing challenges of balancing their modern lifestyle with traditional family expectations in Kerala, leading to a series of heartwarming and comedic situations.

Title: Dear Krishna
Synopsis: A gripping tale of an intense and pure bond between a father and son, woven with threads of joy, anguish, fear, and tranquility.

Title: Dreamcatcher
Synopsis: A software developer experiences haunting lucid dreams that begin to predict future events. As the line between dreams and reality blurs, he delves into the mysterious origin of his visions.

Title: Legends of the Condor Heroes: The Gallants
Synopsis: The Mongols, led by Genghis Khan, went west to destroy the Jin Dynasty, wanted to go south to destroy the Song Dynasty. Martial Arts Masters from several Schools in the Central Plains of China fought gathering strength to defend Xiangyang

Title: Nimma Vasthugalige Neeve Javaabdaararu
Synopsis: This phrase means "You are responsible for your belongings." As humans, there are attachments to belongings, which often intertwine with the deepest insecurities. Unfortunately, many of these insecurities manifest in reality.

Title: Don't Die: The Man Who Wants to Live Forever
Synopsis: Explores a man's quest for immortality and the lengths he goes to defy aging.

Title: Den of Thieves: Pantera
Synopsis: Big Nick is back on the hunt in Europe and closing in on Donnie, who is embroiled in the treacherous world of diamond thieves and the infamous Panther mafia, as they plot a massive heist of the world's largest diamond exchange.

Title: Oficina do Diabo
Synopsis: An ambitious young demon is instructed by an older, more experienced devil on the art and science of condemning a soul to Hell. Dilemmas and hard lessons about the human heart and the fate of a human soul hangs in the balance.

Title: Rhino King
Synopsis: James, a jobless husband, grapples with strained marriage as wife Sarah's career thrives. Left behind, he embarks on self-discovery journey, seeking purpose and worth amidst unfulfilled dreams and marital turmoil.

Title: You're Cordially Invited
Synopsis: When two weddings are double-booked at the same venue, the father of one bride and the sister of the other bride try to preserve the wedding weekend.

Title: Companion
Synopsis: A weekend getaway with friends at a remote cabin turns into chaos after it's revealed that one of the guests is a robot companion.

Title: Star Trek: Section 31
Synopsis: In Star Trek: Section 31, Emperor Philippa Georgiou joins a secret division of Starfleet tasked with protecting the United Federation of Planets, and must face the sins of her past.

Title: Back in Action
Synopsis: Former CIA spies Emily and Matt are pulled back into espionage after their secret identities are exposed.

Title: Flight Risk
Synopsis: A pilot transports an Air Marshal accompanying a fugitive to trial. As they cross the Alaskan wilderness, tensions soar and trust is tested, as not everyone on board is who they seem.

Title: Dog Man
Synopsis: Dog Man, half dog and half man, he is sworn to protect and serve as he doggedly pursues the feline supervillain Petey the Cat.

Title: Wolf Man
Synopsis: A family at a remote farmhouse is attacked by an unseen animal, but as the night stretches on, the father begins to transform into something unrecognizable.

Title: One of Them Days
Synopsis: When best friends and roommates Dreux and Alyssa discover Alyssa's boyfriend has blown their rent money, the duo finds themselves going to extremes in a race against the clock to avoid eviction and keep their friendship intact.

Title: Sky Force
Synopsis: Skyforce unravels a gripping tale inspired by true events from one of the deadliest air strikes between India and Pakistan. A hero lost, a comrade's quest for truth-an epic tribute to bravery, sacrifice, and unbreakable courage.

Title: Ad Vitam
Synopsis: After escaping an attempted murder, Franck Lazareff must find his wife Leo, who has been kidnapped by a mysterious group of armed men. He is caught up by his past and plunged into a state affair that is beyond him.

Title: Henry Danger: The Movie
Synopsis: A theatrical film based on the Nickelodeon Show 'Henry Danger.'

Title: Deva
Synopsis: A brilliant yet rebellious police officer uncovers a web of deceit and betrayal while investigating a high-profile case.

Title: Fateh
Synopsis: Follows a former gangster who is hired to guard a young woman named Khushi. In order to keep her safe, Fateh must employ all of his abilities while simultaneously attempting to learn the truth about the threats made against her.

Title: Chasing the Wind
Synopsis: A focused city worker and a laid-back surfer - both heirs to the same company - find they have plenty in common when they join forces in the boardroom.

Title: Peter Pan's Neverland Nightmare
Synopsis: Wendy Darling strikes out in an attempt to rescue her brother Michael from 'the clutches of the evil Peter Pan.' Along the way she meets Tinkerbell, who will be seen taking heroin, believing that it's pixie dust.

Title: Into the Deep
Synopsis: Modern day pirates on the hunt for sunken drugs kidnap a boat of tourists and force them to dive into shark infested waters to retrieve the contraband.

Title: Alarum
Synopsis: Two rogue spies go off-grid, marry, and come under attack at their remote cabin hideaway by various intel agencies seeking a stolen hard drive.

Title: Sankrathiki Vasthunam
Synopsis: An ex-cop's attempt to rescue a key figure becomes a hilarious juggling act between his wife and former lover.

Title: Game Changer
Synopsis: An honest IAS officer's fight against a corrupt political system through fair and transparent elections.

Title: Bank of Dave 2: The Loan Ranger
Synopsis: This sequel to Bank of Dave sees Dave Fishwick taking on a new and more dangerous adversary: The Payday Lenders

Title: This Is the Tom Green Documentary
Synopsis: Comedian Tom Green's journey takes unexpected turns as he shifts from wild MTV stunts to confronting serious health challenges, ultimately finding peace away from Hollywood on his Canadian farm.

Title: Identity
Synopsis: A sketch artist and a cop work together to unravel the identity of an elusive killer using the descriptions of his face, etched into the memory of an eye-witness to the brutal crime.

Title: Daaku Maharaaj
Synopsis: A daring robber, striving for survival and establishing his own territory amid conflicts with powerful adversaries, battling to become a 'king without a kingdom'.

Title: Dark Nuns
Synopsis: A young boy Hee-Joon is possessed by an evil spirit. Nun Yunia tries to save him, assisted by Nun Mikaela. Priest Paul attempts medical treatment, while Priest Andrew performs an exorcism to rid Hee-Joon of the spirit.

Title: Creation of the Gods II: Demon Force
Synopsis: Taishi Wen Zhong led the army of Shang Dynasty including Deng Chanyu and four generals of the Mo Family to Xiqi. With the help of Kunlun immortals such as Jiang Ziya, Ji Fa led the army and civilians of Xiqi to defend their homeland.

Title: The Gardener
Synopsis: Serge holds a state secret. He, his family and gardener Leo appear on a government death list. They attempt to devise a plan to stay alive.

Title: Lucca's World
Synopsis: Determined to help her son, who has cerebral palsy, Bárbara takes her family to India for an experimental treatment.

Title: Kaadumale
Synopsis: A woman's suicide attempt lands her in a mysterious realm where she meets a man haunted by a supernatural force. Together, they face the dark secrets of their forest prison as time runs out and malevolent powers close in.
